General Online Seller

We get it. You're a busy person with no time for technical stuff.

Our team of tax and importation experts will set up your Federal and Provincial tax accounts and get a Business Number for you. You will also recieve guidance on how to apply for the relevant business licenses needed to operate in Canada.

We will then incorporate all of that into your E-commerce platform, so that you will not have to worry about penalties, fines or back taxes - but will be looking forward to your refund cheques. CTC makes selling online in Canada a stress-free experience.

Exploring Global Expansion

The process of expanding into global markets can be daunting and confusing.
Our team will work with you step by step, from applying for your tax ID to communicating with all required authorities. We will act as a liaison between your company and the Canadian government.

A dedicated team of tax and importation experts handles all inquiries, letters, and requests from the Federal and Provincial tax authorities.

We will tackle your tax-related issues, while you will expand your business to more markets.

Your Obligation as an online seller in Canada

Avoiding tax penalties or termination of seller account

Here is how we can help:

Registration & Tax ID

If you plan on selling in Canada, you must first obtain a TAX ID and a Business Number from the federal and provincial governments. Once registered as a tax collector, you can claim any GST you paid forward to be refunded.

Tax collection and payment

When you sell online, you become a tax collector as well. Generally, you pay wholesale taxes on your entire inventory, collect retail taxes from your customers, and submit to the tax agency the difference between wholesale taxes and retail taxes you collected.

Reporting & Record keeping

Tax-related documents must be meticulously kept. Depending on your online platform, they might be required as proof of compliance, or you'll need them to calculate the maximum GST refund for each reporting period.

We calculate & apply for your GST refund

Let's Talk

It really is this simple!

We deal with the Tax Man - So that you don’t have to!

Register

Your business is registered with the appropriate tax and licensing agencies.

Collect Tax

You collect taxes from your customers on behalf of the government. After you are registered, you do not pay sales tax, but collect it and submit it.

Payment

We will calculate the amount you collected, minus the amount you already paid during import, and submit payment.

Expand, Sell, Ship

All tax related transactions are handled by us so that you can focus on growing your business and expanding into new markets.

Enjoy

As an international seller, expect to recieve a GST REFUND cheque in the mail. You're welcome!

Tax Rules & Rates

by Province

Quebec

Registering under the conventional statute will benefit sellers to reclaim ITC paid out

Min. Worldwide Sales $30k
QST/HST Tax Rate 5% GST
Provincial Tax Rate 9.975% QST
Anual Reporting Frequency Up to $1.5M Annual Sales
Quarterly Reporting Frequency $1.5M - $6M Annual Sales
Monthly Reporting Frequency More then $6M Annual Sales
Zero Rated Goods

Basic Foods, International freight, feminine hygiene, Books with ISBN, Medical, some fishing and farming equipment & products.
